They vary greatly from standard query languages, which are governed by strict syntax rules as command languages with keyword or positional parameters. There are three broad categories that cover most web search queries: informational, navigational, and transactional. These are also called ""do, know, go."" Although this model of searching was"\', \'"Search engine (computing)" | "specify criteria about an item of interest and have the engine find the matching items.
